<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5778&amp;p=53197#p53197"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />What is source control anyways ?<br /></div><br /><br />If I remember correctly, source control (eg CVS or SVN) works kind like a physical library does.  You have a project with all its files and for some reason you want to work on a portion of it so you 'check it out' of the system.  Once you do that nobody else is able to do so.  You work on the portion you checked out and then submit the new version back and the code becomes available again.  If you make a balls-up of it and somebody else notices they can revert it back to the previous version (like you can with a Wiki).<br /><br />Anyhoow, thats how I remember it being taught nearly 10 years ago.<br /><br />edit: tepples beat me to it  <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3210">Hojo_Norem</a> — Sat Nov 28, 2009 11:38 am</p><hr />
